                       <h3 class="lesson-title">4. The Secret Life of Letters & Symbols</h3>
                       <p class="lesson-summary">Ever wonder how your computer stores your name or texts? Uncover the secret codes (like ASCII) that computers use to turn every letter, number, and symbol into binary!</p>
                       <a href="#" class="zelda-button">Start Lesson</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lesson-card">
                       <h3 class="lesson-title">5. Pixel Power! Painting with Binary</h3>
                       <p class="lesson-summary">Zoom in close on a digital photo! Find out how images are made of tiny coloured squares called 'pixels', with each colour stored as a binary number code.</p>
                       <a href="Y7_T6_L5.html" class="zelda-button">Start Lesson</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lesson-card">
                       <h3 class="lesson-title">6. Binary Beats: How Computers Hear Sound</h3>
                       <p class="lesson-summary">How does your favourite song get inside your computer? Explore how sound waves are 'sampled' thousands of times a second and turned into digital 0s and 1s.</p>
